400	     * Rebuilds PlayerRecords from the provided game day onward.
401	     *
402	     * Bootstraps the running per-year and all-time player-record state from
403	     * the most-recent database snapshot per player before `gameDayId`, then
404	     * replays all game days from that point in chronological order. This
405	     * ensures rankings at each rebuilt game day are computed across all known
406	     * players — not only those who happened to play on the specific day being
407	     * processed.
408	     *
409	     * Future game days are excluded because records/standings should only
410	     * reflect completed time periods. Fixtures in the future may already have
411	     * response data, but those should not affect rankings yet.
412	     *
413	     * @param gameDayId - The game day from which records should be rebuilt.
414	     * @returns A promise that resolves to the upserted PlayerRecords.
415	     * @throws Any error thrown by underlying services or database operations if
416	     * rebuilding PlayerRecords fails.
